.TH SEEDTEST-LICENSE 1 "December 2025" "Seed Test Suite 1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
seedtest license \- manage license activation
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B seedtest license
.B \-k
.I key
.PP
.B seedtest license
.B \-\-status
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B license
command manages license activation for Seed Test Suite. A valid license is
required to use the tool beyond evaluation mode.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-k ", " \-\-key " " \fIlicense-key\fR
Activate a license key. Format: XXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXX.
.TP
.BR \-\-status
Display current license status including tier, features, and expiration.
.TP
.BR \-\-deactivate
Deactivate current license (for transferring to another machine).
.SH LICENSE TIERS
.TP
.B Reflector (Tier 1)
Packet reflection functionality only. Suitable for use as a test endpoint.
.TP
.B TestSuite (Tier 2)
Full test suite including RFC 2544, Y.1564, RFC 2889, RFC 6349, Y.1731,
MEF, and TSN tests.
.TP
.B Enterprise (Tier 3)
All features plus REST API, multi-user support, and advanced reporting.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Activate a license:
.PP
.nf
.RS
seedtest license -k ABCD-1234-EFGH-5678
.RE
.fi
.PP
Check license status:
.PP
.nf
.RS
seedtest license --status
.RE
.fi
.PP
Sample output:
.PP
.nf
.RS
License Status: Active
Tier: TestSuite
Features: reflector, rfc2544, y1564, rfc2889, rfc6349, y1731, mef, tsn
Expires: 2026-01-01
Hardware ID: A1B2C3D4E5F6
.RE
.fi
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/seedtest/license.key
System-wide license key storage (root required).
.TP
.I ~/.seedtest/license.key
User license key storage.
